Others: Young arms Julian Aguiar and Rhett Lowder are set to make their MLB debuts for the Cincinnati Reds amidst injuries to the team's rotation.
Julian Aguiar made his third big league start in a game against the Oakland A's on August 30, 2024.
Rhett Lowder, ranked the No. 2 Reds prospect and No. 35 overall prospect by MLB Pipeline, is scheduled to make his Major League debut on August 30, 2024, in a game against the Milwaukee Brewers.
